goal_list_1:
LIST OF GOALS

 

Please describe each of your goals in full sentences below. Your goals can relate to any aspect of your life and you may frame them in whatever way makes the most sense to you. However, please write in a way so that someone who doesn't know you could read this list of your goals and understand them. 



As a reminder, you may list as many or as few goals as you are currently committed to or striving for. If you have more than 5 goals, please write down the first 5 that come to your mind. You should not include any identifiable information in your answers, for example, the full name of your friend.

 

The next button will appear at the bottom of the screen when it is time to move on. - Goal 1

Primary_identity: Self identity is define as the recognition of one's potential and qualities as an individual in relation to social context. In other words, self identity is the opinions of your qualities in relation to other people. Without other people, you wouldn’t need an identity because you wouldn’t need to identify yourself from other people.  Then there is self awareness which is define as conscious knowledge of one's own character, feelings, motives, and desires. Self awareness is very different from self identity. That’s because self awareness has nothing to do with other people and only have to do with yourself.  In life, there are three things that makes up one’s identity.  1.) How you see yourself.  2.) How others see you.  3.) Who you really are.  Sadly, in life, most people are very concentrated on self identity and not enough on self awareness. They are heavily invested on the opinion of themselves and the opinions of others and not enough on who they really are. And one simple way of proving this is to test other people.
